            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Besides colonizing those who grew our tea and voting ourselves out of the common market, the Brits are renowned for various attributes deemed somewhat ‘twee’. Having tea with the Vicar, re-thatching a cottage in the golden autumn sunshine, or planting roses whilst humming ‘",
            "type": "text",
